[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring class loading options**\n\nI’m considering whether to use a public API for loading classes. Maybe Byte Buddy’s public ByteArrayClassLoader could be a solution? However, I need to load the NexusAccessor from a byte array without resources, which complicates things. Is there a public ClassLoadingStrategy that can help? I think net.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader might work based on existing tests. I’m just trying to ensure I correctly load the NexusAccessor and its nested classes!\n\n**Evaluating test outcomes**\n\nI'm considering that this test in native might fail due to the need to define classes after building the image. It seems I need a one-to-one dedicated file already established. Should I add a second test in the same file? I should remember that the classloader uses source bytes from parent resources, and in a native image, those resources may not include class bytes, so I might encounter a failure. I should only catch errors and not IOException.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0575176afed470df016a25258421a881908b06fed4aa4399d1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJSWtk-YNuBpUZ3OFjSFKYVqdqH29o2nRdKgSwTB4aJ0ujl1eifI6yYdze3jefEkZCiUtcRSRhHcLdmG_8yc0vjXSjv30NLMysZztS-itVivnjvQWKw2XvDcnENGc6I3Y_FIMxleAZUdwOZ4EAoyD2pnWIs43zCFy-WgPZYmKnI8QiB0ALdhpuVaFE3rCTSqC9tyZhPqce29edafzrhMQID2v57YGci_zDwKetOqCQZqMVjBNYXMdpsKSZ5mMXPmHLBnjr4iDf4Xpe5dtmSvbM6t95j8lrpib7s-saZ06DCwDLSBH5_ckbBS_ZfxtwmZ14WKlwjEqvA9S4NwXruNl5n30Bl90OZdHWbZvL8fT8XS5EgKZzsXduviqVRuEvottS2ABuRdVBDozPVZxIQT6ok_idT0HYIoKnZXismpkj_5Zr7BLKxtHg8wfkCespG7rc1CsmC3a2GZS-n9QYx4iDVCF7Zd2rCPvOu-d6rMjxpDVggU_82SEPpYN45lgLbhMbTMwCjd9DOoclSLzTjGdBmY0t0aX4XpDa7jdhUivR3K5bG1B9MraQGUs2UGKOXHT4Rp2IHoONfl6T_C3FclXUlCIPahcivrr2vPRifK04VopIcriSsCK4oy1NxeJ8Ja4nrgB9A_lC22RFCzQmL3adu20Pi6WGTkN48vv-b61fsfDZK0JeU827Lc38qM9V5kL0H92muN0VgRygKUR4uMsWTHcCUrnT5