[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class injection**\n\nI’m considering the possibility that class transformers might exclude custom read bytes. I think I might need dynamic access reports strictly for classes from the artifact JAR rather than for custom-defined ones. Therefore, arranging an original class fallback seems essential. I wonder how to ensure the injection fails for the original class since it relies on ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader(). Injecting Nexus into the system could work, given that primary access succeeds if the resource is available.\n\n**Considering subclass access**\n\nI’m exploring the idea of creating a subclass in a test package. It’s interesting because a protected member of a public class is accessible from the subclass, even if it’s in a different package. But then there's the question of static members—how do they fit into this? I need to clarify this distinction as I think about the structure and functionality in the code. It’s a bit tricky, but important to get right!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0575176afed470df016a252695298881909eaef1a265c73526\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJSbDoC5c9lGf08VFs_zAaheP8jwCYpL_5Asi_QPSxmvRzn-enfOuC-TWxNGtscL8L7ZH63YhXdQrlD5ZKTzEWgw19JPkMW00qpPCb74_cpD9RbtUnJxFzkR1pTsx25ALC8xe6ZB_7RBCS-6ktL6IdSPBTOaPcIQLQydlcwHv_0mADVwl0bNpYG6l438shhi9beQTb4AH9GF6lppkuMTakW4fNP2Gw9TyUAbNhkXbpFX0zEiFUhB8c_kYN26ceZvBAbii57aF9ty0r_-JAd40YQQxEM4bjN8SBSQlCrPhz09z2s-iTKylLn28Bd5FDQI9kg_-fq0KtbmBnBXmzDHISwTbaRaqzv2hF36BrWAzdB4SzRkY9-VNc0WHFK7UIHwjyh1JmkQjZzAfuuxHBr3H1C_MGzAJvs1BYmVUb7SMV1ccG75qVM-ARohT9Zz8dY-RtGWiJz66e6wetBQStzMRltbZD3OoJ9a-diY43XHC_i4MpQToE2XqjhdOH8IYS_dS_yACeL8hpY9vn9ZjG628yyr9A1x7BC9pyOuGW_v8phUM6_GRbqf5LepKwTTvWvbxww-DfSmp6EIxlW3U9J07UjsaNBNtF0-uwu8Li2OYfXxAwSZuNQkVfK0jEdXpG6PiihpQQIA4UP80ls6IrWMcSmYYzi1cUDpQ-HoJdk-OZ40lUKrUj0RiBwUQHixr3Bk55_MxP6-E2ccgZdRhZ-_mkFo50qUpni9bj