qsUjadz3MUnHaLGOofGNX5yXNZnUaymkKGpHRy-Fnf3E3l89xIAxLameFrgPVa0dNj5_XNzuK8CauwilGr23PKGPSOQwK6MYqsByurTt-e_mclKyOfiu1VZdSpaz94LbB4515m5IpxeDe9x1m6POGLOJ5gVy6xdtdJhNQzhKGJER0GCqj6KFqAf2FsUHH3eSSKzLeoihbcDsIgdGvhb6Ko8n0Ao9wBGD_fddXNyr9AL2FoH21DdFpzNpQqlY5axW5p3tldr3Eo4zb-NPR2cfPwV7zOiigGm4rUQQ3s9tzy9r-rlHkOWng9pzIrngUZZW_ptGvati0NLDOhqKpmkjqjbDFV1ETivEcSBxrnuKbofuWo8LhanihjdBkfME2elx1SzmqXIYobMLCB9dzHjOcJpzqQ9-fm4i8Ix5EZNVFqmNpmqTq6jE9izCpwXzXoSwgJYSHlWVlik_wxr3tfE1YQ_gOgiZxnE8KE9N6NkN7HczrhOwra_Y3jIbEVD__ovfhPSw_16wksNmEfFaCLOY-9VswsFATfgXGUprHZJB637DjqgY5oyvIs9V01ZAyyXTN45w3HB4wL2atGHvkrn_ztPw8Jip_fcct0WbMQETHnnz_AAqiwBkPsWY44ATGujB-8NDl5zwWpTIM3VvRVsbhNkDnxVKz9ag==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading behavior**\\n\\nI'm trying to understand the behavior of class loading in this scenario. So, if `override getResourceAsStream` returns null for `NEXUS_RESOURCE`, I'm curious about why that would happen. It seems like the internal `loadClass` method for Nexus in `URLClassLoader` uses `findClass` instead, which is an important distinction. This makes me wonder about how resources are managed and accessed. Understanding this could clarify my approach moving forward!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bEG0HTUliqfNAdbojg7eDVEe|fc_0575176afed470df016a2526f25828819081f3a48764fd2e5f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.bytebuddy/byte-buddy/1.8.15/src/test/java/net_bytebuddy/byte_buddy/NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.HashSet;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.Set;\n", "newText": "import java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.HashSet;\nimport java.util.Set;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void fallsBackToSystemNexusWhenClassFileCannotBeLocatedForInjection() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            assertThat(NexusAccessor.isAlive()).isTrue();\n            Map<String, byte[]> typeDefinitions = new HashMap<String, byte[]>();\n            for (String typeName : ISOLATED_TYPES) {\n                typeDefinitions.put(typeName, readClassBytes(typeName));\n            }\n\n            ResourceHidingClassLoader classLoader = new ResourceHidingClassLoader(typeDefinitions);\n            Class<?> nexusAccessorType = Class.forName(NexusAccessor.class.getName(), true, classLoader);\n\n            assertThat(nexusAccessorType.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] readClassBytes(String typeName) throws IOException {\n        String resourceName = typeName.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n        InputStream inputStream = NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.class\n                .getClassLoader()\n                .getResourceAsStream(resourceName);\n        if (inputStream == null) {\n            throw new IOException(\"Cannot locate class resource: \" + resourceName);\n        }\n        try {\n            ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n            byte[] buffer = new byte[1024];\n            int length;\n            while ((length = inputStream.read(buffer)) != -1) {\n                outputStream.write(buffer, 0, length);\n            }\n            return outputStream.toByteArray();\n        } finally {\n            inputStream.close();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class ResourceHidingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final Map<String, byte[]> typeDefinitions;\n\n        ResourceHidingClassLoader(Map<String, byte[]> typeDefinitions) {\n            super(NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.class.getClassLoader());\n            this.typeDefinitions = typeDefinitions;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                if (typeDefinitions.containsKey(name)) {\n                    Class<?> type = findLoadedClass(name);\n                    if (type == null) {\n                        byte[] binaryRepresentation = typeDefinitions.get(name);\n                        type = defineClass(name, binaryRepresentation, 0, binaryRepresentation.length);\n                    }\n                    if (resolve) {\n                        resolveClass(type);\n                    }\n                    return type;\n                }\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n        }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void fallsBackToSystemNexusWhenClassFileCannotBeLocatedForInjection() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            URL byteBuddyLocation = Nexus.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation();\n            ResourceHidingClassLoader classLoader = new ResourceHidingClassLoader(\n                    new URL[] {byteBuddyLocation},\n                    NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.class.getClassLoader());\n            try {\n                Class<?> nexusAccessorType = Class.forName(\n                        \"net.bytebuddy.dynamic.NexusAccessor\",\n                        true,\n                        classLoader);\n\n                assertThat(nexusAccessorType.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n            } finally {\n                classLoader.close();\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private s